Class SocketServerHandler

java.lang.Object
org.mio.progettoingsoft.network.client.socket.SocketServerHandler
All Implemented Interfaces:
Remote, VirtualServerSocket, VirtualServer
public class SocketServerHandler extends Object implements VirtualServerSocket
SocketServerHandler acts as the client's proxy for communicating with the server via Sockets. It implements the VirtualServerSocket interface, allowing the client to invoke "server-side" methods (which are actually sent as messages over the socket) and providing a concrete way for the client's ClientController to interact with the game logic on the server.
